iversity Style Guide          Logos          Campus Announcements          Photography          Banners          Campus Film Office          UIC Licensing Program          Endorsement Policy          IGNITE Campaign Style Guide             About the office      Joshua Clark    Institutional Marketing  Marketing and Brand Management develops and executes strategic marketing campaigns designed to strengthen the university’s reputation and identity as a leading academic and research institution.  Sustaining a strong brand image for the university is critical in promoting awareness, understanding and support among students, faculty, staff, alumni, donors, opinion leaders, and the broader public.  Marketing Support to Units  In addition to marketing UIC at an institutional level, the Office of Marketing and Brand Management is available to provide integrated marketing communications support to the university’s schools, colleges and programs. The staff focuses its efforts on projects that align with UIC’s strategic priorities. The office works with units to define goals, objectives, strategies and tactics to help ensure that marketing communications projects are successful and cost-effective.                     UIC Logo         The  University of  Illinois  at  Chicago           UIC Offices    Office of the UIC Chancellor    Office of the UI President    UI Office of Governmental Relations    UI Alumni Advocacy    UI Foundation      Public and Government Affairs Sites    UIC Today    Brand Resources    RED WordPress multisite    Office of Public and Government Relations    Disability Resources    Emergency Information    Privacy Policy    Contact Us         Contact   1330 University Hall 601 S. Morgan St.  Phone: (312) 996-3456  marketing@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube    Tumblr             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openi